small town between here and Houston, German

01:45.879 --> 01:54.531
community down there. And Darryl was in the Corps. 
And I used to hire undergraduates and still like to

02:00.174 --> 02:05.199
hire undergraduates to work with us some. And he 
worked with us some in the lab when he was in the

02:06.300 --> 02:14.187
Corps and come in and had his uniform on from time to 
time. And finally, he decided, well, he'd do his

02:15.588 --> 02:18.111
master's degree. And I told him, that's fine. I 
have a friend in Germany. whom I had developed a

02:25.797 --> 02:40.985
working relationship through this book 
publishing cycle that I'd gotten into, Udo

02:25.797 --> 02:40.985
Svirtman, and I said, he'd probably be glad to have 
you come over and work something with him. And so he

02:42.407 --> 02:48.278
did, and he was the first in our lab to use the magnet 
to take iron compounds out of soil. And we knew this

02:53.447 --> 02:58.135
process had been developed, but we hadn't brought 
it down to a laboratory scale. He used a magnet over

02:59.076 --> 03:01.921
in engineering, actually, to do that. And Darrell 
Schultz then applied and received a von Humboldt

03:02.782 --> 03:15.362
scholarship and went to Germany and worked with my 
colleague Schwertmann and got his doctor's

03:02.782 --> 03:15.362
degree there. And he's on the faculty at Purdue 
University and has been there for several years

03:16.287 --> 03:23.958
and has been very successful there. And he and I are 
co-editors on this last book, which is

03:24.839 --> 03:30.748
gratifying. Of all the students you've had, 
reckon what percentage are in academia, what

03:31.068 --> 03:41.603
percentage are in government, what percentage 
are out in private industry? They're scattered

03:43.405 --> 03:46.169
throughout the three different areas. I guess 
academia would maybe have a slight edge. Some are

03:54.562 --> 03:56.145
consultants. Just last week I called Hugh Durham, 
and Hugh got his master's here. He's a South Texas

04:02.655 --> 04:09.025
boy and married a young Greek lady when he was in the 
military. And they were here, and his children

04:09.646 --> 04:18.460
were small, and he was pressed by finances and 
didn't get a PhD, and went with a clay company in

04:09.646 --> 04:18.460
Georgia. And now he's in Gonzales with the 
Southern Clay Products Company, and he's

04:19.201 --> 04:27.614
marketing clay products for them. And I called him 
last week and talked to him, and he was in Memphis,

04:28.475 --> 04:36.868
north of Memphis, when I caught him in the car over 
there.

04:38.958 --> 04:41.000
For a master's student, he's done well. And down 
through the years, could you tell much difference

04:42.641 --> 04:54.652
between the preparation, once they were in your 
class, of the engineers, the geoscientists, the

04:42.641 --> 04:54.652
ag people? Was there much difference between how 
capable they were to do the work in their course?

05:03.860 --> 05:08.965
They tend to have a better developed background 
mathematically. in engineering. And they tend to

05:11.018 --> 05:15.169
have a better background chemically in soil 
science. And those are the main differences. And

05:20.082 --> 05:21.486
as time goes on, They blend, but in general, it's 
pretty hard for people who never, engineers are

05:21.635 --> 05:31.565
taught chemistry, but they don't use it day to day 
like we have to use it. And therefore, that's kind

05:31.585 --> 05:35.810
of a hurdle that they have to gradually work over. 
But the beauty of this course, like I had a student

05:36.610 --> 05:47.001
from India who was in civil engineering. He was a 
real promoter for the course. He recruited

05:51.706 --> 05:54.349
students from us over there. And he's now, I think, 
with a consulting firm. But he was really a spark

06:00.996 --> 06:04.620
plug at whatever he did. And it was because he could 
see through this. And our ultimate customer is

06:11.407 --> 06:16.532
really the public. And he was one who saw the full 
breadth of that. And he had to do very engineering

06:21.952 --> 06:31.041
type of work when he was here and worked quite a lot 
with me mineralogically and with my research

06:21.952 --> 06:31.041
associate. But when he got over there, he had to 
apply it in a totally different way to highway

06:31.702 --> 06:40.310
instability and things like that. But he went out 
then. to serve in the public. And he's the second

06:46.499 --> 06:54.429
engineer that I've had that had an international 
background who went out, the first one went with a

06:46.499 --> 06:54.429
state highway. And these, my point is that we can't 
very often get a chance to help much with roads and

06:54.449 --> 07:05.503
foundations because our research is not We're not 
tied as closely to that. But these students, they

07:09.391 --> 07:12.697
take this right out into the field. And so that's 
among the more gratifying experience I've had

07:13.378 --> 07:26.985
with students, realizing that Texas is plagued 
with millions of acres of very reactive clay

07:13.378 --> 07:26.985
soils. And, you know, if you drive the streets of 
this community, you know that painfully. Well,

07:32.669 --> 07:43.675
even today I was talking with one of my colleagues 
in Extension about how we could do something to

07:32.669 --> 07:43.675
help handle the urban scene, not just the rural 
scene, but the urban scene. as to how to better

07:43.857 --> 07:51.530
utilize these soils and stabilize them and get the 
water to flow where it should and not where it does.

07:52.311 --> 08:01.326
And being able to work with this diverse group has 
permitted us to reach out quite a bit to them. In

08:01.346 --> 08:09.460
these students and their effort, I have the 
impression that Asian students are extremely

08:01.346 --> 08:09.460
diligent. Can you generalize about the diligence 
of students by their background? Just their

08:15.365 --> 08:17.748
determination, their effort? It is true that the 
Asian students do tend to be very diligent. At the

08:23.895 --> 08:30.544
Masters and PhD level, the students in general are 
more motivated. So having to prod students is not

08:30.904 --> 08:36.932
our usual circumstance.

