Now, there's a lot of difference. I've had not many 
students from Japan, although I've had a few, but

08:39.059 --> 08:45.990
I've had some postdocs from Japan. And they are 
very methodical, and they can work on the most

08:47.012 --> 09:02.937
ragged problem, and their consistency and 
persistence they can deal with. whereas

09:03.845 --> 09:06.469
Americans would probably not have the patience. 
But coming up as they have, and as it happens,

09:08.131 --> 09:16.343
Japanese soils are volcanic soils, very 
disorderly and very difficult to deal with. They

09:18.085 --> 09:26.597
made progress, and I've had the privilege of 
working with three different Japanese. Have you

09:27.899 --> 09:30.122
ever had any... events that obviously showed some 
kind of awkwardness between some students

09:31.351 --> 09:43.512
because of their, the history of their countries. 
A student from Greece and Turkey working side by

09:44.914 --> 09:55.452
side or Korea and Japan working side, any of that 
ever? I've thought about that many times, and

09:57.068 --> 10:01.795
that's really a rare thing. I had a student came in 
from South Africa, actually, he was a postdoc

10:01.935 --> 10:06.923
here. And he said when he got here, he said, you 
know, it was quite an experience to come from South

10:07.644 --> 10:17.518
Africa and come in through South America. Said we 
kind of went from the black to the brown. He said,

10:22.853 --> 10:25.478
that was really a jolt to my wife and I. And he was not 
prejudiced. He was a white child. Yes, he was

10:29.826 --> 10:32.090
white. And he was very diligent, very capable, 
very efficient. And it wasn't long until Abu

10:37.520 --> 10:46.397
Sinkai from Uganda, who's very African, They were 
just exchanging views. And so it's sort of a

10:50.887 --> 10:58.457
mystery to me that people have trouble that they do 
when I see these guys working together. What about

10:58.818 --> 11:14.680
any awkwardness of male-female, a Muslim, a woman 
from a Muslim background dressing in a fashion

10:58.818 --> 11:14.680
that might not be acceptable back home or 
something or other? I don't believe I've had a

11:14.913 --> 11:18.336
Muslim woman. I remember when I went to Saudi 
Arabia and I met my friends from over there. They

11:24.583 --> 11:27.706
came out in their white attire. And I just 
commented, you know, all this grand welcoming

11:28.887 --> 11:35.193
beginning and all this workshop we were going to 
have. They had brought in people from all the

11:35.253 --> 11:43.401
neighboring Arab countries, which I found later 
they had to pay their way to get them to come. And I

11:44.528 --> 11:51.322
just said privately at lunch or something, it's a 
mysterious thing I've observed here. You all have

11:51.342 --> 11:57.475
such a, Riyadh is growing and thriving, and yet 
there are no women. I just don't know how you've

11:58.357 --> 12:00.782
managed all this. They sure didn't come back with 
any quick

12:01.741 --> 12:06.706
answers. But even then I could see these young 
ladies that they were beginning to educate with

12:06.726 --> 12:16.757
their briefcases and going to the record shops and 
that music and things. But I haven't had any, I've

12:18.118 --> 12:28.609
had, now I did have a young woman, now that you 
mention that, The poorest country neighbor to

12:28.589 --> 12:33.851
India on the east. It's in the wetlands. I think 
it's Bangladesh. She was my class, and she's

12:41.243 --> 12:43.907
Muslim. But she said, when I discussed that type of 
thing with her privately, she said, well, when I

12:44.308 --> 13:01.132
first came, I wore my attire one day, but said, you 
know, it seemed to be sort of a problem, so I haven't

12:44.308 --> 13:01.132
been wearing it anymore. Her father was a civil 
engineer. And they were actually originally from

13:05.022 --> 13:11.311
India, I think, and they were working in that part 
of the world. But she was very bright and very

13:12.032 --> 13:17.721
capable and did well in the course. So I was 
pleased, because I've always had a particular

13:19.223 --> 13:25.532
empathy for the women in that part of the world. 
Have you ever had any student of any sort give you

13:29.930 --> 13:40.801
some kind of hokum kind of excuse that they can't do 
something or other because of, or they need

13:29.930 --> 13:40.801
special consideration because of? I had a 
sabbatical person from Egypt who was devout, is

13:40.821 --> 13:47.769
devout Muslim. And the thing that he did that I, he 
didn't press this on us, but every so many times a

13:48.650 --> 13:56.798
day, he rolled out his mat and did his prayers in the 
laboratory. Oh, so he really did. And I made a point

14:04.850 --> 14:12.601
not to go into the laboratory when he was prayer 
